<!-- MAIN -->
<main>

<!-- COVER -->
<div class="cover" id="brief">
  <div class="cover-meta">SEO Director's Brief &nbsp;·&nbsp; Board of Directors &nbsp;·&nbsp; Q1 2026</div>
  <h1>Organic Search<br>in a <em>Restructuring</em><br>SERP Environment</h1>
  <p class="cover-abstract">
    Organic search delivered +31% revenue growth on a higher-quality, lower-volume traffic base — a structural outcome of AI Overview disruption and deliberate content repositioning. The business case for continued SEO investment in 2026 rests not on recovering click volume, but on capturing the commercial intent signal that AI Overviews leave behind.
  </p>
  <div class="cover-stats">
    <div class="cstat">
      <div class="cstat-label">Organic Revenue</div>
      <div class="cstat-val">$67.6K</div>
      <div class="cstat-delta d-up">+31.4% YoY</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cstat">
      <div class="cstat-label">Organic AOV</div>
      <div class="cstat-val">$1,084</div>
      <div class="cstat-delta d-up">+41.6% YoY</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cstat">
      <div class="cstat-label">Impressions</div>
      <div class="cstat-val">3.38M</div>
      <div class="cstat-delta d-up">+45.4% YoY</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cstat">
      <div class="cstat-label">Organic Clicks</div>
      <div class="cstat-val">18,649</div>
      <div class="cstat-delta d-down">−11.2% YoY</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cstat">
      <div class="cstat-label">Blended CTR</div>
      <div class="cstat-val">0.55%</div>
      <div class="cstat-delta d-down">from 0.90% PY</div>
    </div>
    <div class="cstat">
      <div class="cstat-label">Rev / Session</div>
      <div class="cstat-val">$2.48</div>
      <div class="cstat-delta d-up">from $1.22 PY</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- SECTION 1: ORGANIC REVENUE -->
<section id="organic-revenue">
  <div class="section-header">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">01 &nbsp; Performance</div>
    <h2>Organic Search as a <em>Revenue Channel</em></h2>
  </div>

  <p class="lead">Google Organic is the only channel in the portfolio posting simultaneous gains in both revenue and session quality. Revenue grew +31% to $67.6K while average order value increased 42%, revenue per session doubled, and engagement time held at 56 seconds. This is not a traffic story. <strong>It is a buyer quality story.</strong></p>

  <div class="row-asym">
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-label">Organic Revenue vs. Other Channels (Shopify)</div>
      <div class="chart-wrap" style="height:260px"><canvas id="chRevChart"></canvas></div>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="card" style="margin-bottom:16px">
        <div class="card-label">Organic Channel Scorecard</div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="sl-name">Revenue (Shopify)<small>Last non-direct click</small></div>
          <div class="sl-val">$67,621</div>
          <div class="sl-yoy up">+31.4%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="sl-name">Average Order Value<small>vs. $765 prior year</small></div>
          <div class="sl-val">$1,084</div>
          <div class="sl-yoy up">+41.6%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="sl-name">Revenue per Session (GA4)<small>vs. $1.22 prior year</small></div>
          <div class="sl-val">$2.48</div>
          <div class="sl-yoy up">+103%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="sl-name">Sessions (GA4)<small>Organic search, all sources</small></div>
          <div class="sl-val">26,046</div>
          <div class="sl-yoy down">−16%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="sl-name">Engagement Rate (GA4)<small>vs. 69.4% prior year</small></div>
          <div class="sl-val">61.5%</div>
          <div class="sl-yoy down">−7.9pp</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-line">
          <div class="sl-name">Avg. Engagement Time (GA4)<small>Quality session signal</small></div>
          <div class="sl-val">56 sec</div>
          <div class="sl-yoy flat">stable</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="pullquote">
    <p>"Fewer organic sessions generating significantly more revenue is the expected signature of AI Overviews filtering out the researchers and leaving the buyers. This dynamic is a feature of the current environment, not a failure."</p>
    <cite>Search Quality Signal — Q1 2026 Analysis</cite>
  </div>

  <div class="row3">
    <div class="finding teal">
      <div class="finding-head"><span class="f-tag teal">Validated</span><span class="finding-title">AOV increase is structural</span></div>
      <p>The +42% AOV increase is not a one-order anomaly. It reflects the product mix shift (tents + inflatables replacing tablecloth volume) combined with higher-intent commercial queries surfacing buyers earlier in the purchase cycle. Organic search is self-selecting for the B2B event buyer.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="finding amber">
      <div class="finding-head"><span class="f-tag amber">Watch</span><span class="finding-title">Engagement rate decline</span></div>
